Professor Adrian Puren, Head of Centre of HIV and STIs at National Institute of Communicable Diseases speaks to #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Coronavirus Command Council is meeting on Sunday as adjusted level four lockdown restrictions, announced two weeks ago, come to an end. Professor Adrian Puren from the National Institute of Communicable Diseases says the cabinet will have a tough time making a decision. READ: COVID-19: Govt starts weekend vaccinations after securing funding Meanwhile, South Africa’s COVID-19 infections remain alarmingly high. The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) reported 21,610 new COVID-19 cases. A total of 265 more deaths takes the death toll to 64,138. Watch the video above for more details